news.title: Planning authorities asked to inform Odisha RERA about housing project approvals
news.para: The move came after Prime Minister Narendra Modi, while chairing a Pragati review meeting, asked the state govts to strengthen ORERA and ensure proper execution of its orders in the interest of homebuyers.

news.title: Adarsh Colony razed, Chandigarh administration considers declaring city ‘slum free’
news.para: Deputy commissioner (DC) Nishant Kumar Yadav said, "We will request the UT administration to declare the city ‘slum free' as all the major slum clusters standing on government land have been demolished.

news.title: Bengaluru development body rolls back hike on initial deposit for flats & villas
news.para: The decision comes in the wake of sustained complaints from the public, who found the increased deposit requirement unaffordable and a barrier to accessing home loans.

news.title: Bombay HC permits slum rehabilitation on up to 65% encroached open space
news.para: The petition said the regulation significantly dilutes the purpose of reservation, denuding the city of much-needed green and open spaces.

news.title: BMC begins survey of Lower Parel land five months after SC rejects Century Textiles claim
news.para: A table survey, akin to a police panchnama, is conducted to record the current ground reality of any plot, capturing details such as the number of structures, encroachments, obstructions, and even tree cover, a civic official explained. "This entire process should take our staff over a month," said the official.

news.title: Nashik civic body plans to auction properties of 73  tax defaulters in first week of July
news.para: In the first phase, Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) will auction the properties of 73 property tax defaulters who have left dues unpaid after issuance of warrants for confiscation of properties.

news.title: Delhi HC to examine appeal of Bhoomiheen Camp residents on rehabilitation rejection
news.para: The petitions also challenged the green signal given to DDA by a single-judge bench of HC to remove encroachments and clear the land near Kalkaji area.

news.title: Gurugram: Structural audits of highrises stalled, panel urges DTCP to come up with SOPs
news.para: The recommendation was made because some structural audits of societies in the city have been delayed or stalled due to disputes between developers and RWAs on bearing the cost of the inspections.

news.title: Chennai: Chetpet residents flag houses turning into commercial units
news.para: In a meeting chaired by Dr N Ezhilan, Thousand Lights constituency MLA, members from Harrington Road Residents Association said houses in the area were rented out as hotels, cafes, and parlours.

news.title: Delhi: Signature View Apartments residents start vacating flats
news.para: The residents' welfare association said that numerous other residents were prepared to relinquish their keys, contingent upon DDA deciding on transferring the compensatory rent as stipulated by Delhi High Court.

news.title: Chennai: 22 sea-facing buildings on ECR face demolition after CRZ violations flagged
news.para: The identified buildings—some completed, others still under construction—are located within the No Development Zone (NDZ) of CRZ III, where permanent structures are banned within 200 metres of the High Tide Line.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 20 years gone, Madhuban Bapudham plot allottees told to shell out lakhs
news.para: Affected buyers now face an average additional cost of Rs 5,175 per sqm, that is Rs 5.17 lakh for a 100 sqm plot and Rs 15.5 lakh for larger plots up to 300 sqm. The plots were earlier sold to them at Rs 11,800 per sqm.

news.title: Nagpur: Over 900 families in Wathoda PMAY flats living in fear of electrocution, water woes
news.para: Developed by Nagpur Improvement Trust (NIT) under the central government's PMAY scheme, the project was meant to offer affordable housing. However, residents allege poor construction quality, unsafe electrical fittings, water shortages, and lack of drainage pose serious risks.

news.title: Those dumping C&D in Krishna river will face action: Swachh Andhra Corporation chairman
news.para: Following media reports of unidentified builders illegally dumping C&D waste in the riverbed near the cremation ground in Ramalingeswara Nagar, Pattabhi Ram, along with Vijayawada Municipal Corporation (VMC) officials, conducted a surprise inspection and examined the C&D debris dumped in the river.

news.title: Margao residents oppose draft master plan, seek proper study
news.para: The presentation in the town hall of the Margao municipal building was attended by a fraction of citizens who were able to fit inside and who could show up following the 48-hour public notice.

news.title: RBI issues project finance norms for banks, NBFCs
news.para: The Reserve Bank of India (Project Finance) Directions, 2025 lay down the revised regulatory treatment upon change in the 'date of commencement of commercial operations' (DCCO) of such projects in the backdrop of a review of the extant instructions and analysis of the risks inherent in such financing.

news.title: Brad Jacobs' QXO offers $5 billion for GMS, threatens to go hostile
news.para: This is Jacobs's second hostile takeover threat in the building sector this year and part of his plan to turn QXO into a $50 billion revenue building-products distributor within a decade.

news.title: Adani can’t sub-lease its data centre project to another company until it’s complete: Noida authority
news.para: The decision marks a reversal of the Authority's earlier stance, with officials insisting they would not allow any relaxation from original allotment conditions.

news.title: Arisinfra Solutions' IPO subscribed 1.32 times on Day 2 of offer
news.para: The category for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) got subscribed 3 times while the portion for non-institutional investors fetched 1.39 times subscription. The quota for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) received 73 per cent subscription.
